<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,151,535]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,223,248]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ros-Farre &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Kovalev" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[331,472,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aspicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kerzhneri">
<emphasis box="[331,472,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">A. kerzhneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ros-Farre &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Belizin" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[533,649,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aspicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foveata">
<emphasis box="[533,649,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">A. foveata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the only 
<taxonomicName box="[810,1001,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aspicera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[810,909,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Aspicera</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
having scutellar spine almost absent, represented only by a distal elongation of the circumscutellar carina. According to the figures of 
<bibRefCitation author="Kovalev, O. V." box="[1258,1436,260,284]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="282 - 289" refId="ref61995" refString="Kovalev, O. V. (1974) On the fauna of Cynipoidea (Hymenoptera) of the Mongolian People's Republic. - pp. 282 - 289. In: Insects of Mongolia &quot;. Issue 2. Nauka Press, Leningrad." type="book chapter" year="1974">Kovalev (1974)</bibRefCitation>
both species can be differentiated by the scutellar foveae: in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ros-Farre &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Kovalev" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[825,961,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aspicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kerzhneri">
<emphasis box="[825,961,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">A. kerzhneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are well defined, about 1/3 scutellum length and with three longitudinal carinae inside while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ros-Farre &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Belizin" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[811,926,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aspicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foveata">
<emphasis box="[811,926,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">A. foveata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are very shallow, at least 1/2 scutellum length and with two longitudinal carinae inside. The original description of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Belizin, 1952)" authorityName="Ros-Farre &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Belizin" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[1046,1349,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aspicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foveata">
<emphasis box="[1046,1163,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">A. foveata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Belizin, V. I." box="[1183,1340,367,391]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="290 - 305" refId="ref60370" refString="Belizin, V. I. (1952) Gall wasps of the family Aspicerinae (Hymenoptera, Cynipidae) of the USSR. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, (32), 290 - 305." type="journal article" year="1952">Belizin, 1952</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kovalev, 1974)" authorityName="Ros-Farre &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Kovalev" baseAuthorityYear="1974" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aspicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kerzhneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">A. kerzhneri</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kovalev, O. V." box="[274,442,404,428]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="282 - 289" refId="ref61995" refString="Kovalev, O. V. (1974) On the fauna of Cynipoidea (Hymenoptera) of the Mongolian People's Republic. - pp. 282 - 289. In: Insects of Mongolia &quot;. Issue 2. Nauka Press, Leningrad." type="book chapter" year="1974">Kovalev, 1974</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
provide more characters to distinguish this species: in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ros-Farre &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Belizin" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[1090,1206,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aspicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foveata">
<emphasis box="[1090,1206,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">A. foveata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the occiput and the lateral surface of propodeum are not carinate, the mesoscutum has some punctuations, while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ros-Farre &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Kovalev" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[1253,1393,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aspicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kerzhneri">
<emphasis box="[1253,1393,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">A. kerzhneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the occiput has longitudinal carinae dorsally and transverse carinae ventrally, the lateral surface of propodeum is carinate transversely and the mesoscutum has transverse carinae.
</paragraph>
